page.title=Install joyn standalone service
doc.type=tools
@jd:body
<div class="background-sdk">
	<div class="content-block" style="min-height:700px;">
		<div class="intro center">
			<p><h1>Install and configure joyn standalone service</h1></p>
			<p><span>On some devices the joyn service stack may not be installed. If this is the case, we provide a joyn-service test application. Once these services are configured appropriately, your Rich Communication application will be able to communicate with them via joyn APIs.</span></p>
		</div>
		<div class="content-body center">
			<div class="guide-block">
					<p><h2>1. Install application</h2></p>
					<p>First copy <a href="{@docRoot}tools/joyn-core.apk">joyn-core</a> to the directory of your choice.</p>									
					<p>To install the application, connect your device via USB. Make sure that USB debugging is active.</p>
					<p>Locate Android SDK on your file system and run the following command from the platform-tools directory.</p>
					<p><code style="background-color:#e1e1e1;">adb install PATH_TO\joyn-core.apk</code> - Replace <span style="font-style:italic">PATH_TO</span> with the location of the apk on your file system.</p>
			</div>
			</br>
			<div class="guide-block">
				<p><h2>2. Automatic Configuration</h2></p>
				<p>Once joyn-core.apk installed, there will be two new applications present on your device as well as the joyn services.</p>
				<div style="width:100%;display:inline-block;margin-bottom:15px">
					<div style="width:60%;float:right;margin:75px 5% 0 0">
						<p>First open the application named <b>Provisioning</b> and go to the second tab named <b>Stack</b>.</p>
						<p>Before trying a manual configuration it is possible that your configuration may be done automatically. To do so, select <b>HTTPS</b> as <b>Auto config mode</b> option and press <b>Save</b>.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="img-ssh">
						<img src="{@docRoot}assets-sdk/images/tuto_ss_prov.png" width="100%"  />
					</div>
				</div>
				<div style="width:100%;display:inline-block;">
					<div class="img-ssh" style="float:right;">
						<img src="{@docRoot}assets-sdk/images/tuto_ss_settings.png" width="100%"  />
					</div>
					<div style="width:60%;float:left;margin:75px 5% 0 0">
						<p>The joyn services must now be restarted.</p>
						<p>You can either restart your device or use the second application named <b>Settings</b>.</p>
						<p>By toggling the first option <b>joyn service</b> you can turn joyn services on and off.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				</br>
				</br>
				<p>If the automatic configuration succeeded, the joyn icon in the notification bar should turn yellow. If this is the case you can now use joyn APIs to communicate with these services.</p>
				<p>Otherwise you must proceed with the manual configuration.</p>						
			</div>
			</br>
			<div class="guide-block">
				<p><h2>3. Manual Configuration</h2></p>
				<p>Return to <b>Provisioning</b> application and go to the second tab named <b>Stack</b>.</p>
				<p>Select <b>none</b> as <b>Auto config mode</b> option and press <b>Save</b>.</p>
				<div style="width:100%;display:inline-block;margin-bottom:15px">
					<div style="width:60%;float:right;margin:75px 5% 0 0">
						<p>Now go to the first tab named <b>Profile</b>.</p>
						<p>Press <b>Generate profile</b>.</p>
						<p>Fill-in the form as asked by entering your phone number, then by selecting the platform you are <b>supposed</b> to connect to.</p>
						<p>Press <b>OK</b>.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="img-ssh">
						<img src="{@docRoot}assets-sdk/images/tuto_ss_prov2.png" width="100%"  />
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>You must now restart joyn services as described in <b>Step 2</b>.</p>
			</div>
			</br>
			</br>
		</div>
		
	</div>
</div>